ogsch building]] \nBogsch was featured in the 1988 Swiss documentary film ''A Szellem Tulajdona'' (''Property of the Intellect''), directed by [[Zolt\u00e1n Bonta]].<ref>{{IMDb title | id= 0378830 | title= A Szellem Tulajdona }}</ref>\n\nThere have been a number of tributes made in Bogsch's memory. The main building at WIPO headquarters in [[Geneva]] is named the \"\u00c1rp\u00e1d Bogsch building\" in his honor.<ref>{{cite web |title=Agreement with General Contractor Paves Way for Beginning of Conference Hall Construction |url=http://www.wipo.int/pressroom/en/articles/2011/article_0016.html |website=WIPO |accessdate=September 9, 2017 |language=en |date=May 31, 2011}}</ref> The Hungarian Intellectual Property Office, in the country of Bogsch's birth, features a [[Bust (sculpture)|bust]] of Bogsch by sculptor {{ill|Tibor Borb\u00e1s|hu|Borb\u00e1s Tibor}}.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u00c1rp\u00e1d Bogsch (1919 - 2004 )|url=http://www.hipo.gov.hu/en/news/sztnh-hirek/hirek-esemenyek/arpad-bogsch-1919-2004 |accessdate=September 9, 2017 |agency=Hungarian Intellectual Property Office |date=July 15, 2012 |language=en}}</ref> The [[International Federation of Inventors' Associations]] in 2010 established the \u00c1rp\u00e1d Bogsch Memory Medal, to be awarded to individuals who support invention and innovation in the same spirit as Bogsch.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u00c1rp\u00e1d Bogsch Memory Medal: The highest international recognition of invention and innovation supporters |url=http://www.invention-ifia.ch/Bogsch/Bogsch%20medal.htm |website=International Federation of Inventors' Associations |accessdate=September 9, 2017 |date=November 24,  2013}}</ref>\n{{clear}}\n\n==Notable works==\n* {{cite book |last1=Bogsch |first1=Arpad |title=Universal Copyright Convention: An Analysis and Commentary |date=1958 |publisher=Bowker |location=New York |lccn=58-13137 |oclc=902072883}} A comprehensive annotation of the [[Universal Copyright Convention]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{start box}}\n{{succession box|title=Director General of [[World Intellectual Property Organization]] (WIPO)|before=[[Georg Bodenhausen]]|after=[[Kamil Idris]]|years=1973&ndash;1997}}\n{{end box}}\n\n{{WIPODirectorGeneral|state=uncollapsed}}\n\n{{Authority control|VIAF=79383740}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bogsch, Arpad}}\n[[Category:1919 births]]\n[[Category:2004 deaths]]\n[[Category:Hungarian emigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:World Intellectual Property Organization people]]\n[[Category:American officials of the United Nations]]\n{{Hungary-bio-stub}}\n{{US-law-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Vahurzpu", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:Move authority control to Wikidata", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%81rp%C3%A1d_Bogsch"}
